# Development experience

Stomp4J is a library — there is no `main()` or dev server. Local validation is **build + tests** and optionally a **Docker broker**.

## Quick start

```bash
mvn verify                    # full build + tests (Docker required)
mvn -pl client test           # client module only
docker compose -f scripts/docker/docker-compose.yaml up   # optional local Artemis
```

## When adding or changing a feature

Before marking work done:

1. **Unit tests** in `commons` for protocol/framing changes.
2. **Integration tests** in `client` or `server` for end-to-end STOMP behaviour.
3. Reuse `StompContainer` for broker-backed tests.
4. Update [docs/features.md](../../docs/features.md) when user-visible capabilities change.
5. Update [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) if module boundaries, SPI, or WIP status change.
6. Update [docs/domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md) for new protocol terms.

## Optional manual check

With `docker-compose` Artemis running, exercise client APIs from a small scratch class or existing README examples against `stomp://localhost:61613`.

## Checklist before finishing

- [ ] `mvn verify` passes (Docker running)
- [ ] New behaviour has tests in the correct module
- [ ] [docs/features.md](../../docs/features.md) updated if capabilities changed
- [ ] ARCHITECTURE.md §12 updated if gaps were closed or discovered

## Never

- Ship protocol changes without `commons` tests and at least one integration test when client/server behaviour changes.
- Rely on manual-only verification when automated tests are feasible.
